Non-invasive methods of examination in the diagnosis of aneurysms. Radionuclide angiography and ultrasonic echolocation were used for the examination of 38 patients with aneurysms. Isotope angiography was fulfilled in all the 38 patients, ultrasonography was used in 20 patients. Radionuclide angiography and ultrasonography are thought to be sufficiently effective methods of diagnosis of vessel aneurysms.